entries.title: Israel and Sudan Agree to Revive Peace Deal
entries.description: Israel said a signing ceremony to normalize relations could take place in Washington in a few months, after Sudan establishes a civilian government.

entries.title: Global Minimum Tax Deal Advances
entries.description: International officials are moving ahead with their tax increases while giving U.S. companies a temporary break from some increases in hopes of prompting the U.S. to implement the deal.

entries.title: Ukraine War Drives Rapid Growth in South Korea's Arms Exports
entries.description: The country has been supplying the U.S. and its allies and is coming under pressure to aid Kyiv directly.

entries.title: Australia to Remove British Monarchy From Its Bank Notes
entries.description: New $5 note will honor the country’s indigenous peoples but the leader of the opposition dismissed it as ‘woke nonsense.’

entries.title: How a Radioactive Capsule Was Lost and Found in the Australian Outback
entries.description: Authorities now want to know how the tiny cylinder shook loose from a truck and whether anyone is to blame.

entries.title: Netanyahu, Macron to Discuss Iran's Nuclear Ambitions in Paris
entries.description: The leaders of Israel and France will meet amid growing Western concerns over the threat posed by Tehran.

entries.title: BOE Raises Key Rate by Half Percentage Point
entries.description: The Bank of England raised its key interest rate for a 10th straight policy meeting, but signaled it may soon pause that series as the annual rate of inflation falls and the economy falters.

entries.title: Iran Threatens Response to Israeli Drone Attack
entries.description: Iran blamed Israel for the first time for a drone attack last month on a military facility in the city of Isfahan and said it reserved the right to “respond resolutely.”

entries.title: Fears of Losing Out to China Put U.S. Under Pressure Over Kenya Base
entries.description: Kenya is asking the U.S. to pay for the expansion of a joint counterterrorism base, raising concerns in Washington that the East African country could turn to China if the Americans balk.

entries.title: Russia Claims Gains in Battle for Bakhmut
entries.description: Russian forces said they had made new advances in their effort to encircle the eastern Ukrainian city of Bakhmut, while European leaders arrived in Kyiv to discuss further military aid.

entries.title: U.S., Philippines Strike Military-Base Deal
entries.description: The U.S. reached an agreement that gives it access to four more military bases in the Philippines, broadening Washington’s efforts to counter China’s influence.

entries.title: North Korea Accuses U.S. of Raising Tensions
entries.description: Pyongyang cited recent promises by the U.S. defense chief to expand joint drills with South Korea.

entries.title: EU Doubles Ukraine Military Training Effort
entries.description: The European Union will double the number of Ukrainian troops it trains to 30,000, a senior EU official said, in a sign of the bloc’s continued support for Kyiv’s war effort.

entries.title: Ukraine Ramps Up Corruption Fight
entries.description: Authorities raided the home of a billionaire who had backed Volodymyr Zelensky’s successful presidential run in 2019.
